<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1440,1635,1884]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
The dorsal color of male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1934" box="[549,683,1636,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Discophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porsena">
<emphasis box="[549,683,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">D. porsena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(mean FW length = 
<quantity box="[943,1051,1635,1659]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.77" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="27.7">27.7 mm</quantity>
[26.7-29.0, n = 7]) in 
<collectingRegion box="[1322,1440,1635,1659]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
varies from brown to red-brown. The macules on the ventral hindwing vary as do those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mabille and Boullet" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1273,1433,1667,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dyscophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diaphorus">
<emphasis box="[1273,1433,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">D. diaphorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male genitalia are as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bell, E. L." box="[620,755,1699,1723]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" pagination="89 - 96" refId="ref18787" refString="Bell, E. L. 1934. New American Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society 29: 89 - 96." type="journal article" year="1934">Bell (1934)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1440,1635,1884]" lastBlockId="26.[192,1440,195,507]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
The relationships of the taxa included by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, W. H." box="[755,918,1731,1755]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans (1952)</bibRefCitation>
and Mielke (2004, 2005) as subspecies (or synonyms) of 
<taxonomicName box="[365,565,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramusis">
<emphasis box="[365,565,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Papilio ramusis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName authority="Hewitson, 1876" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1876" box="[707,1178,1763,1787]" genus="Eudamus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="astrapaeus">
<emphasis box="[707,971,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Eudamus astrapaeus</emphasis>
Hewitson, 1876
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Plotz, 1882" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Netrocoryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="damias">
<emphasis box="[1191,1440,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Netrocoryne damias</emphasis>
Plötz, 1882
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bell, 1934" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1934" box="[345,741,1795,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Discophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porsena">
<emphasis box="[345,606,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Discophellus porsena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bell, E. L." box="[613,741,1795,1819]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" pagination="89 - 96" refId="ref18787" refString="Bell, E. L. 1934. New American Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society 29: 89 - 96." type="journal article" year="1934">Bell, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" box="[806,1165,1795,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dyscophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ramusis" subSpecies="ramon">
<emphasis box="[806,1165,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Dyscophellus ramusis ramon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, need to be examined. The morphologies of the valvae of these taxa, as indicated by descriptions and figures (
<bibRefCitation author="Bell, E. L." box="[1204,1319,1827,1851]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" pagination="89 - 96" refId="ref18787" refString="Bell, E. L. 1934. New American Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society 29: 89 - 96." type="journal article" year="1934">Bell 1934</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayward, K. J." pageId="24" pageNumber="23" refId="ref19607" refString="Hayward, K. J. 1948. Insecta, Lepidoptera (Rhopalocera), familia Hesperiidarum, subfamiliae Pyrrhopyginarum et Pyrginarum. Vol. 1. In: H. R. Descole (ed.). Genera et Species Animalium Argentinorum. Guillermo Kraft; Buenos Aires. 389 p." type="book" year="1948">Hayward 1948</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, W. H." box="[263,407,1859,1883]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans 1952</bibRefCitation>
), show differences as great as those between unquestionably recognized species within 
<taxonomicName box="[192,354,1728,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dyscophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,354,1728,1752]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Dyscophellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Wing shape and colors differ (
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, W. H." box="[733,878,1728,1752]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans 1952</bibRefCitation>
) and both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1007,1123,1729,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dyscophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramon">
<emphasis box="[1007,1123,1729,1752]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. ramon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1882" box="[1183,1310,1728,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Netrocoryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="damias">
<emphasis box="[1183,1310,1728,1752]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. damias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been treated as full species (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Bridges, C. A." box="[521,683,1760,1784]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" refId="ref18914" refString="Bridges, C. A. 1988. Catalogue of Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera). Published by the author; Urbana. 443 p." type="book" year="1988">Bridges 1988</bibRefCitation>
, Warren 2000). 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, W. H." box="[873,1031,1760,1784]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans (1952)</bibRefCitation>
provisionally included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1934" box="[1311,1440,1761,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Discophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porsena">
<emphasis box="[1311,1440,1761,1784]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. porsena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[390,584,1793,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dyscophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ramusis" subSpecies="astrapaeus">
<emphasis box="[390,584,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. r. astrapaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is incorrect since not only do the genitalia differ from that taxon, its color is different: “ochreous brown” (
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, W. H." box="[658,799,1824,1848]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans 1952</bibRefCitation>
) for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[852,1042,1825,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dyscophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ramusis" subSpecies="astrapaeus">
<emphasis box="[852,1042,1825,1848]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. r. astrapaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and “rusty-red” (
<bibRefCitation author="Bell, E. L." box="[1246,1359,1824,1848]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" pagination="89 - 96" refId="ref18787" refString="Bell, E. L. 1934. New American Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society 29: 89 - 96." type="journal article" year="1934">Bell 1934</bibRefCitation>
) for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1934" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Discophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porsena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. porsena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Also, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1934" box="[370,501,1857,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Discophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porsena">
<emphasis box="[370,501,1857,1880]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. porsena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[622,682,1857,1880]" name="Peru" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Peru</collectingCountry>
and western 
<collectingCountry box="[846,925,1856,1880]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, within the distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stoll" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[1252,1388,1857,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dyscophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramusis">
<emphasis box="[1252,1388,1857,1880]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. ramusis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and away from that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[425,626,1889,1912]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dyscophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ramusis" subSpecies="astrapaeus">
<emphasis box="[425,626,1889,1912]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">D. r. astrapaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in northern South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, W. H." box="[991,1141,1888,1912]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" refId="ref19451" refString="Evans, W. H. 1952. A Catalogue of the American Hesperiidae in the British Museum. Part II (Groups B, C, D), Pyrginae. Section I. British Museum (Natural History); London. 178 p." type="book" year="1952">Evans 1952</bibRefCitation>
, Mielke 1973, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cock, M. J. &amp; S. Alston-Smith" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" pagination="25 - 35" refId="ref19128" refString="Cock, M. J., and S. Alston-Smith. 1990. The skipper butterflies (Hesperiidae) of Trinidad. Part 6: Pyrgine, genera group D. Living World 1989 / 1990: 25 - 35." type="journal article" year="1990">Cock and Alston-Smith 1990</bibRefCitation>
). For these reasons, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1934" box="[684,816,196,219]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Discophellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porsena">
<emphasis box="[684,816,196,219]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="25">D. porsena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here raised from synonymy and recognized as a species-level taxon.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4532853" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4532853" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4532853/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="24" startId="25.[192,276,1549,1571]" targetBox="[196,1432,196,1522]" targetPageId="25">
<paragraph blockId="25.[192,1441,1549,1687]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,384,1549,1571]" pageId="25" pageNumber="24">Figure 104-110.</emphasis>
